issue.title: Add new SQL Server role management commands (Get-SqlDscRole, New-SqlDscRole, Remove-SqlDscRole)
issue.body: This PR implements three new public commands for managing SQL Server roles, addressing the need for programmatic server role operations using the SMO ServerRole API. ## New Commands ### Get-SqlDscRole Retrieves server roles from a SQL Server Database Engine instance with support for: - Getting all server roles when no name is specified - Getting a specific role by name - Refreshing the server's roles collection before retrieval - Pipeline input support ```powershell $serverObject = Connect-SqlDscDatabaseEngine -InstanceName 'MyInstance' $allRoles = $serverObject | Get-SqlDscRole $specificRole = $serverObject | Get-SqlDscRole -Name 'MyCustomRole' ``` ### New-SqlDscRole Creates new server roles in a SQL Server Database Engine instance with support for: - Setting the role owner during creation - Force parameter to bypass confirmation prompts - Validation to prevent creating duplicate roles - ShouldProcess support for safe operations ```powershell $serverObject = Connect-SqlDscDatabaseEngine -InstanceName 'MyInstance' $newRole = $serverObject | New-SqlDscRole -Name 'MyCustomRole' -Owner 'MyOwner' ``` ### Remove-SqlDscRole Removes server roles from a SQL Server Database Engine instance with support for: - Two parameter sets: by server object + name or by role object - Protection against removing built-in roles (validates `IsFixedRole` property) - Force parameter to bypass confirmation prompts - ShouldProcess support with high impact confirmation ```powershell $serverObject = Connect-SqlDscDatabaseEngine -InstanceName 'MyInstance' $serverObject | Remove-SqlDscRole -Name 'MyCustomRole' -Force # Or using role object $role = $serverObject | Get-SqlDscRole -Name 'MyCustomRole' $role | Remove-SqlDscRole -Force ``` ## Implementation Details - **Follows existing module patterns**: Uses the same error handling, localization, and SMO integration patterns as other commands in the module - **Comprehensive error handling**: Includes proper exception handling with localized error messages using `New-InvalidOperationException` - **Type safety**: Uses strongly-typed SMO objects (`Microsoft.SqlServer.Management.Smo.ServerRole`) for all operations - **Localization support**: All user-facing strings are localized using the module's string resource system - **Full test coverage**: 33 comprehensive unit tests covering all scenarios including success paths, error conditions, parameter validation, and edge cases ## SMO Integration The commands leverage the existing SMO infrastructure in the module: - Uses `Microsoft.SqlServer.Management.Smo.ServerRole` objects - Integrates with the server's `Roles` collection - Follows SMO patterns for object creation (`New-Object` + `.Create()`) and deletion (`.Drop()`) - Supports role property management including `Owner` and `IsFixedRole` validation All commands follow the module's naming convention using the `SqlDsc` prefix and `Role` noun as specified in the requirements. --- üí° You can make Copilot smarter by setting up custom instructions, customizing its development environment and configuring Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers. Learn more [Copilot coding agent tips](https://gh.io/copilot-coding-agent-tips) in the docs. - - - This change is‚ÄÇ[](https://reviewable.io/reviews/dsccommunity/SqlServerDsc/2137)

pull_request.title: Test Coverage for post-release & pre-release & associated post-fix merge branch fix
pull_request.body:
Looking over github actions, there didn't seem to be a good way to "test" them.  Most defer the action to a script and then test that script.  However, these actions make heavy use of git & there isn't a practical way to test them ... other than using Git.  I've added a basic mock framework to assist in testing our git actions so going forward we can expand test coverage.  I've started with adding tests for the pre & post release actions.  

I went down this path because of this failure: https://github.com/apache/grails-core/actions/runs/16727197839/job/47769435724 

This PR should resolve this failure - the issue was the action wasn't stripping the refs/heads from the refspec to checkout the associated branch for update.

issue.title: Support for DuckDB
issue.body:
<!---
Please don't remove the template.
Please be sure the feature does not yet exist with the latest HeidiSQL build from https://www.heidisql.com/download.php#nightlybuilds
-->

**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
No problem, except that my favorite DB GUI doesn't support this database yet.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
DuckDB is a lot like Sqlite, but optimized for analytical processing. It's also completely free. It would just be very nice if HeidiSQL supported this database type too. Information can be found here:

https://duckdb.org/

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
I'm using commandline and the built-in webgui. This works, but not great. DBeaver and Beekeeper studio support it too.

pull_request.title: Issue: #330 Implement Transaction Management for Atomic Operations
pull_request.body:
CLOSES: #330

## Summary
- Implemented DatabaseTransaction utility class for atomic operations
- Automatic transaction support detection with graceful fallback to standalone MongoDB
- Updated all critical multi-write UserService operations to use transactions
- Enhanced User model with session-aware instance methods
- Comprehensive test coverage including unit and integration tests

## Changes Made
### Core Implementation
- **DatabaseTransaction.ts**: New utility class providing MongoDB transaction support
  - `withTransaction()`: High-level transaction wrapper
  - `withSession()`: Manual session management
  - `isTransactionSupported()`: Auto-detection of replica set support
  - `withFallback()`: Graceful degradation for standalone instances

### Database Layer Updates
- **UserServiceDatabase.ts**: All multi-write operations now use transactions
  - `markEmailVerified()`: Atomic email verification + token clearing
  - `updatePasswordAndClearTokens()`: Atomic password reset operations
  - `generateAndSaveResetToken()`: Atomic token generation
  - `generateAndSaveEmailToken()`: Atomic email token generation

### User Model Enhancements
- **User.ts**: Updated instance methods to accept session parameters
  - `generatePasswordResetToken()`: Now supports transactions
  - `generateEmailVerificationToken()`: Now supports transactions
  - `updateLastLogin()`: Now supports transactions

### Service Layer Integration
- **UserServiceAuth.ts**: Enhanced user creation process with atomic operations
  - User creation + email token generation now atomic
  - Improved error handling for transaction failures

### Testing
- **DatabaseTransaction.test.ts**: Comprehensive unit tests with mocking
- **UserServiceTransaction.integration.test.ts**: Real database integration tests
- All existing functionality maintained with backward compatibility

## Benefits
‚úÖ **Data Consistency**: Multiple database writes are now atomic
‚úÖ **Reliability**: No more partial state from failed operations
‚úÖ **Backward Compatibility**: Works with both replica sets and standalone MongoDB
‚úÖ **Error Handling**: Graceful fallback when transactions aren't supported
‚úÖ **Performance**: Minimal overhead with automatic detection
‚úÖ **Test Coverage**: Comprehensive testing of all transaction scenarios

## Test Results
- ‚úÖ All unit tests pass
- ‚úÖ Build completes successfully
- ‚úÖ Linting passes with no errors
- ‚úÖ Transaction fallback mechanisms work correctly
